From 1b9117db4c288378a7cd0bcb4d6a20ef62340473 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 18:23:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] EXPERIMENT E-UNION: wire copy-up/whiteout into write-op
 emulation sites (PoC, #ifdef EUNION)

Add three thin policy helpers in vchroot_userspace.c that the syscall
emulation sites call so the union policy stays in one place:
  vchroot_prepare_write(guest)  copy-up lower->upper (or clear whiteout) BEFORE
                                a write/mutate so the real syscall never touches
                                the shared read-only template
  vchroot_post_unlink(guest)    AFTER a successful unlink/rmdir, drop a whiteout
                                iff the name still exists in the lower template
  vchroot_pre_mkdir(guest)      BEFORE re-creating a name, clear any whiteout

Wire 13 path-translating mutating sites (absolute guest paths only; relative /
out-of-prefix is a no-op in the helper):
  openat (write/create/trunc), truncate, fchmodat, chmod_extended, utimes,
  mkdirat, mknod, mkfifo, symlinkat, linkat, unlinkat, rmdir, renameat.

All additions are #ifdef EUNION -> production builds (no -DEUNION) are
byte-identical to baseline (verified: zero E-UNION symbols without the flag).
The three helpers are TDD-proven in experiments/e-union (60 assertions green,
stable across runs).

Not yet wired (needs per-fd merge state + real-fd plumbing the hermetic loop
cannot exercise): getdirentries -> vchroot_readdir_merge. fchownat/lchown are
no-op stubs upstream; setxattr does not vchroot_expand its path (pre-existing).
rename of a lower-only DIRECTORY only copies up the top dir, not descendants
(gVisor F.3 recursion) -- documented limitation for the PoC.

Local only, nothing pushed.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
